name: 16S rRNA (adenine1518-N6/adenine1519-N6)-dimethyltransferase
reaction: 4 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine1518/adenine1519 in 16S rRNA = 4 S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N6-dimethyladenine1518/N6-dimethyladenine1519 in 16S rRNA
comment: KsgA introduces the most highly conserved ribosomal RNA modification, the dimethylation of adenine1518 and adenine1519 in 16S rRNA. Strains lacking the methylase are resistant to kasugamycin [1].
